article.description: Eyassu Worku scored 19 points, Evan Leonard added 18, and UC Irvine beat Hawaii 70-63 on Saturday night.
article.headline: Worku, Leonard help UC Irvine beat Hawaii 70-63
article.linkText: Worku, Leonard help UC Irvine beat Hawaii 70-63
article.story: HONOLULU -- Eyassu Worku scored 19 points, Evan Leonard added 18, and UC Irvine beat Hawaii 70-63 on Saturday night. Collin Welp added 15 points for UC Irvine, which has won six in a row against Hawaii. Welp made two free throws to give UCI (17-10, 9-2 Big West Conference) a 13-point lead with 2:26 to play but Drew Buggs and Justin Webster answered with back-to-back 3-pointers to spark a 10-0 run that made it 66-63 when Zigmars Raimo made a layup with 36 seconds left but Leonard and Worku each made a pair of foul shots to cap the scoring. Buggs led Hawaii (14-10, 5-5) with 17 points and seven assists and Eddie Stansberry scored 10 points. The Rainbow Warriors have lost their last four games.
